That the words in brackets give
						the approximate sense seems clear from , ;
						but it is difficult to get it out of the Greek.

This sentence is not finished;
						the parenthesis which follows lasts until the end of the
						chapter.

Anaxagoras. What he really meant was that even
						the sweetest things contain some bitter particles. Cf. ;
						Burnet, E.G.P. 129.
